189
00:19:51,596 --> 00:19:53,057
This is a wonderful step.

190
00:19:53,117 --> 00:19:53,977
It's going to be a great year.

191
00:19:54,297 --> 00:19:54,918
Thank you very much.

192
00:19:55,763 --> 00:20:08,534
I'm here with Dr. Michelson and Mrs. Michelson, Dr. Marano, and Mr. Terrabelsi, all wonderful supporters over many, many years of the Lawrence Memorial Hospital, as has this council.

193
00:20:09,395 --> 00:20:21,385
And I want to thank this council very much for the last four or five years, you've been working with us towards an affiliation for the Lawrence Memorial Hospital and Hallmark Health that's going to strengthen

194
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:26,304
the healthcare services in this city for generations to come, in my opinion.

195
00:20:26,924 --> 00:20:49,184
And as you know, we just, as of January 1 of this year, two days ago, became effectively partnered with Tufts Medical Center and Circle Health, which is Lowell General Hospital in Lowell, which is a major hospital, uh, to work with Hallmark Health, three founding members of a new parent organization called Wellforce.

196
00:20:50,052 --> 00:21:03,620
And we will be equal members on the board of trustees for that charitable parent organization, seven trustees from our community, seven from Tufts Medical and seven from Lowell.

197
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:12,545
And we will be making investments in our healthcare facilities and services for again, the next generation to come.

198
00:21:13,403 --> 00:21:20,286
And I wanted to bring that news in person at your invitation, Mr. President, because it is momentous.

199
00:21:21,406 --> 00:21:25,768
As you know, we've had 92 and a half years, almost 93 years for the Lawrence.

200
00:21:26,668 --> 00:21:42,515
And the last couple of years, as healthcare has changed, as the patient base is using acute care hospitals in a little different way, because so much more can be outpatient and ambulatory, but we still have a lot of need for inpatient care.

201
00:21:43,246 --> 00:22:02,739
And so we need to adjust to make sure that we're offering the level of services for the future that will warrant investment in the Lawrence, particularly, and that will draw the patient volume to match our capability to provide the services.

202
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:10,705
We have tremendous talent in terms of physicians and nurses and technical staff at the Lawrence.

203
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:15,270
Where, as Dr. Michelson always says to me, we're open for business.

204
00:22:15,350 --> 00:22:16,131
And yes, we are.

205
00:22:16,191 --> 00:22:17,933
We have been for 92 plus years.

206
00:22:18,433 --> 00:22:21,215
And we intend to be for some time to come.

207
00:22:22,156 --> 00:22:23,217
And that's our goal.

208
00:22:23,457 --> 00:22:37,129
And we find in partnering with Tufts Medical Center in particular, which means so much to this community, that the university itself and the School of Medicine, which are apart from the center, but they're all part of the same network.

209
00:22:37,949 --> 00:22:45,752
that they, all of those organizations, were so excited that we were interested in becoming part of their network.

210
00:22:46,312 --> 00:22:52,655
And we're going to see over the next few years' time more of what we call specialty services in the community.

211
00:22:53,395 --> 00:22:55,296
And that's a tremendous step for us.

212
00:22:56,436 --> 00:23:05,760
As we've discussed with this council over the last few years, we have looked at partnerships with other people, and this council has been supportive of that.

213
00:23:06,297 --> 00:23:09,118
seven to zero, and we appreciate it very, very much.

214
00:23:09,998 --> 00:23:18,261
Uh, what happened is, you know, the state itself, Commonwealth of Massachusetts, wanted us to look at all the options that might be available to us.

215
00:23:18,861 --> 00:23:28,304
Well, there were many, and we had wonderful business proposals from a number of organizations that were very proud to say, wanted to be associated with Hallmark Health.

216
00:23:29,024 --> 00:23:29,504
In the end,

217
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:39,979
For us to see a governance opportunity where we could have a lot to say about the future of our community in the larger network, that was what was most attractive.

218
00:23:40,400 --> 00:23:49,364
Much more than just reporting to a larger organization and waiting to hear what the organization felt was most important to our community.

219
00:23:49,844 --> 00:23:53,345
