243
00:26:27,937 --> 00:26:36,440
The short answer is no, and you always want to say, for what time, to the year 2340, or what is it?

244
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:41,681
What my communication team always tells me, nothing changes until it does change.

245
00:26:42,501 --> 00:26:44,322
Everything stays the same until it changes.

246
00:26:44,502 --> 00:26:56,365
Our intention is to continue for as long as we can look ahead at our ability to provide urgent care, emergency care, and acute care at the Long Island Memorial Hospital.

247
00:26:57,256 --> 00:27:11,349
We have been making some changes because we need to make sure that we can attract the investment to reinvest in the Lawrence that will see a volume to match the investment.

248
00:27:11,369 --> 00:27:18,495
So we are trying to judge what the patient base is most interested in, in terms of using the facility.

249
00:27:18,676 --> 00:27:23,340
Naturally, we've done as we have in the past in the orthopedics and

250
00:27:23,868 --> 00:27:26,830
I just had a discussion now about our interest in pediatrics.

251
00:27:26,870 --> 00:27:31,594
We have a strong interest in trying to figure out how to do more in that area if we can.

252
00:27:32,114 --> 00:27:42,321
But we're looking at a number of different areas that we'd like to do more in that with the help of Tufts Medical Center we might be able to do that we might not be able to do on our own.

253
00:27:43,002 --> 00:27:50,287
And so what complements each one of those systems and services is what the future will dictate for us.

254
00:27:50,862 --> 00:27:56,664
But certainly our intention is to maintain what we have now and grow from there.

255
00:27:56,684 --> 00:28:00,105
Uh, and uh, there's no timetable on it.

256
00:28:00,145 --> 00:28:00,685
That's the thing.

257
00:28:00,725 --> 00:28:11,548
When people ask me as they have asked you, I've been involved since the 1980s with the hospital folks here have been involved a little longer, but that's a pretty good long stretch.

258
00:28:12,089 --> 00:28:16,470
But I've been asked since the 1980s almost each and every year, are we going to do

259
00:28:17,210 --> 00:28:18,951
forever certain things at the Lawrence.

260
00:28:18,991 --> 00:28:22,672
And I say, well, you asked me 10 years ago, we're still doing it.

261
00:28:22,712 --> 00:28:24,093
Five years ago, we're still doing it.

262
00:28:24,573 --> 00:28:28,094
It's possible 25 years from now, we would be doing something different.

263
00:28:28,595 --> 00:28:38,979
It's very important for us to look at what the changes in the healthcare industry are so that we maintain our presence at the Lawrence Memorial Hospital.

264
00:28:38,999 --> 00:28:44,501
Some communities, as we know, don't have that presence anymore because they didn't adapt.

265
00:28:44,581 --> 00:28:46,702
They weren't able to attract the investments.

266
00:28:47,177 --> 00:28:53,759
We think we're going to attract investments and recruit more talent to what we have in this arrangement.

267
00:28:53,819 --> 00:28:55,139
And that's the future for us.

268
00:28:56,219 --> 00:29:02,421
But if we cannot attract the investment or cannot attract the recruiting of top talent, there won't be the future.

269
00:29:02,801 --> 00:29:03,761
We think there will be.

270
00:29:03,821 --> 00:29:04,802
That's our game plan.

271
00:29:04,842 --> 00:29:05,722
That's what we're going to do.

272
00:29:06,542 --> 00:29:12,904
So just if I could, Mr. President, the merger that was going to happen with Partners Healthcare.

273
00:29:13,204 --> 00:29:13,344
Yes.

274
00:29:14,635 --> 00:29:18,536
From what I understand, Lawrence Memorial Hospital is going to be more of a cardiac center.

275
00:29:19,456 --> 00:29:26,157
There was going to be a psychiatry area within Lawrence Memorial, an expanded psychiatry area.

276
00:29:27,058 --> 00:29:38,280
Now with Tufts, are we going to be looking at a different focus of specialties or will the focus still be on the focuses that were with Hallmark Health and enhancing those specialties?

277
00:29:38,963 --> 00:29:45,531
That is the exact discussion that we're having even this month, and we've had all the way up, and we're going to have through this year.

278
00:29:46,072 --> 00:29:49,496
We're very strong in behavioral health, as you know, at the Lowndes.

279
00:29:50,718 --> 00:29:55,043
We, with partners, looked at the opportunity

280
00:29:55,585 --> 00:30:00,829
to continue using Lawrence in a way that it is now on acute care overnight stay.

281
00:30:01,529 --> 00:30:07,713
We used to have, as you know, 134 bed license that was fairly active well back.

282
00:30:08,334 --> 00:30:15,919
We're still very active in certain areas, but the size of that 134 beds is more than we would need.

283
00:30:15,999 --> 00:30:18,321
As I've said during the discussions,

284
00:30:19,081 --> 00:30:33,106
with the partners people, if we invested for 134 acute care beds at the Lawrence, it wouldn't get the use and it wouldn't pay back the investment, and then we would be without a hospital.

285
00:30:33,667 --> 00:30:42,690
If we, with partners, that was a different plan, but with partners, if we invested for 30 to 35, what they called short-term beds and other medical services,

286
00:30:43,611 --> 00:30:55,958
you would be in a position because that was similar to what the use was when we talked to partners to grow and that if we in 10 years needed 60 beds or a hundred beds, we would be there to grow.

287
00:30:56,419 --> 00:31:05,404
Whereas if we over invest and over promise and we can't pay back the investment, we go the way of some of those other community hospitals that don't exist.

288
00:31:05,824 --> 00:31:10,367
And then 10, 15 years when you're ready for it, we're not there to grow.

289
00:31:11,103 --> 00:31:17,126
But if we invest for the way that the population and patient base wants to use the facility,

290
00:31:17,890 --> 00:31:29,833
and we have the volume and the community support that you've given us and that the community generally will give us, then we're in a position to grow again as things change, because nothing stays the same as we know.

291
00:31:29,873 --> 00:31:35,954
There's a flow on the way different services provide.

292
00:31:35,994 --> 00:31:43,576
We don't need as much open heart surgery as once upon a time, because there's less invasive stuff that we can do for cardiology.

293
00:31:44,076 --> 00:31:45,937
All of these services change over time.

294
00:31:45,957 --> 00:31:47,137
So you make the investments.

295
00:31:47,736 --> 00:31:55,177
But they don't last for 25, 30 years because the technology changes, the medical intelligence changes.

296
00:31:55,798 --> 00:32:02,759
We just want, we want to be available for what the near term is to be able to continue growing for the longer term.

297
00:32:03,419 --> 00:32:10,901
And that includes in our mind, emergency department, it includes urgent care, it includes certain acute care needs as well.

298
00:32:11,481 --> 00:32:17,482
But exactly what that is, we have to do that now in discussion with Tufts Medical Center, not just ourselves.

299
00:32:18,094 --> 00:32:21,935
What we like about this is they care as much about our community as we do.

300
00:32:22,615 --> 00:32:32,898
And we're now going to be working with somebody that has more resources, more reach for other resources, and, uh, an ability to help us recruit more talent.

301
00:32:34,198 --> 00:32:38,640
If you can keep us in touch every step of the way, be helpful like you've been doing.

302
00:32:39,020 --> 00:32:39,620
I want to do that.

303
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:40,320
Thank you, Mr. President.

304
00:32:40,560 --> 00:32:41,320
Thank you very much.

