00:33:12,212 --> 00:33:15,217
Well, we're going to stay strong in internal medicine.

314
00:33:15,238 --> 00:33:18,844
We're going to stay strong in cancer care.

315
00:33:20,227 --> 00:33:24,875
We're going to stay strong in our system on maternal health.

316
00:33:27,666 --> 00:33:29,546
Those things are very important to us.

317
00:33:30,146 --> 00:33:32,467
We will stay strong in behavioral health as well.

318
00:33:32,527 --> 00:33:42,770
That's an area that we've got a long history in, and the Commonwealth needs a lot of help in that area, frankly, and we'd like to be part of that help.

319
00:33:43,431 --> 00:33:47,892
So these are all things that we care tremendously about, and then it's a matter of

320
00:33:48,517 --> 00:33:51,701
recruiting the talent in the areas that we want to be good in.

321
00:33:53,444 --> 00:33:56,007
And we continue.

322
00:33:56,087 --> 00:34:02,756
I always say to my gang, you can win the Super Bowl and it doesn't mean you skip the draft the next year.

323
00:34:02,816 --> 00:34:05,600
You're still recruiting off the top of the draft if you can.

324
00:34:06,347 --> 00:34:13,252
We've got a tremendous amount of talent, but we're always looking to grow that talent base because things change.

325
00:34:14,032 --> 00:34:17,755
People come and go, and technology changes, as I say.

326
00:34:17,795 --> 00:34:21,718
So we want to continue to be strong in all the places that I mentioned.

327
00:34:22,258 --> 00:34:30,464
But like in any system, again with the flow, you become stronger in certain areas, and then you try to go in other areas as well.

328
00:34:30,504 --> 00:34:31,664
But you play to your strength.

329
00:34:31,784 --> 00:34:35,267
And our strength has been in cardiology, internal medicine,

330
00:34:36,171 --> 00:34:39,953
uh, cancer care, as I say, maternal health.

331
00:34:40,713 --> 00:34:45,015
And we really see an opportunity in pediatrics to do more.

332
00:34:45,615 --> 00:34:51,817
As you know, over the years, we used to deliver babies at the Lawrence, my brother and sister, my older brother and sister were born there.

333
00:34:52,798 --> 00:34:53,738
And, uh, there you go.

334
00:34:53,838 --> 00:34:55,759
And my mother was a Cambridge girl.

335
00:34:55,799 --> 00:34:57,860
My dad was, but my mother was Cambridge.

336
00:34:57,880 --> 00:34:59,600
She had me at Cambridge city hospital.

337
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:00,501
I was a third.

338
00:35:00,521 --> 00:35:01,361
I don't know what happened.

339
00:35:02,713 --> 00:35:06,675
But we stopped delivering babies at the Lawrence, but we do other things.

340
00:35:07,136 --> 00:35:10,839
And so you can't tell what the long, long term is going to be.

341
00:35:10,859 --> 00:35:17,283
But in the immediate term, it is to strengthen what we already have, and then to see where that takes us.

342
00:35:17,804 --> 00:35:23,108
But if we're working as we are going to be with a world class outfit, Tufts Medical Center was established in 1796.

343
00:35:25,241 --> 00:35:31,024
It was founded by Paul Revere and Sam Adams and a few of those folks.

344
00:35:31,544 --> 00:35:34,706
We're going to be tying in with some people who know how to stick around.

345
00:35:35,466 --> 00:35:36,286
And we do too.

346
00:35:37,107 --> 00:35:39,388
And we want to build on that.

347
00:35:39,925 --> 00:35:55,432
We don't know exactly what that means for 2025 or 2030 or 2035, but to us it means that we're going to have a team that wants to be here, that wants to grow and stay with whatever the technology on medical care is.

348
00:35:56,192 --> 00:36:16,438
And one of the things, we've talked about it here and privately among ourselves, that some of the things that we used to do in the hospital and go in for four or five days with, let's say, a hernia operation or a gallbladder operation, we used to go in for four or five days and be told not to move in the bed.

349
00:36:16,478 --> 00:36:21,499
Now we have an afternoon, they take care of us and send us home and call in the morning and say, I hope you're okay.

350
00:36:21,879 --> 00:36:23,620
And we are okay, because we had great talent.

351
00:36:24,080 --> 00:36:24,921
There were other things.

352
00:36:25,021 --> 00:36:32,808
One of the things, what happens is when we get patients in the hospital now, they're sicker patients than once upon a time in a sense.

353
00:36:34,149 --> 00:36:36,011
I do remember speaking with my dear mother.

354
00:36:36,491 --> 00:36:39,114
She would say, she had seven children.

355
00:36:39,154 --> 00:36:45,239
She said, I love it when I have one of you because they put me in there for a whole week and I get a week off, she would say to me.

356
00:36:47,663 --> 00:36:48,463
when you have a baby.

357
00:36:49,063 --> 00:36:51,044
So they're just a very different thing.

358
00:36:51,444 --> 00:36:53,305
And it'll be different in 2025.

359
00:36:54,005 --> 00:36:56,026
But we want to be part of it, whatever it is.

360
00:36:56,586 --> 00:36:58,366
And that's what we're trying to do.

361
00:36:58,826 --> 00:36:59,627
We're going to grow with it.

362
00:37:00,007 --> 00:37:03,808
And then to follow up on that, I know the partnership's going to help greatly.

363
00:37:04,668 --> 00:37:06,109
What resources are there?

364
00:37:06,169 --> 00:37:09,050
What better things can we do to make sure we're growing with the times?

365
00:37:10,810 --> 00:37:12,371
Financially, how will we be able to do that?

